     "desc": "Create a cinematic realistic film still of a wounded Asian man standing under a vast clear blue sky, captured from a dramatic low-angle perspective as if the camera is looking up at him from below. He has messy medium-length black hair blown slightly by the wind, a tired but intense expression, and a small fresh cut on his cheek with subtle blood stains. He wears a dusty beige suit jacket over a dark shirt, the fabric slightly dirty and worn, suggesting he has just survived a violent confrontation or difficult journey.\n\nThe composition should feel lonely, powerful, and cinematic, with the man positioned slightly left of center and a large amount of empty sky filling the background. Use natural harsh daylight, strong contrast, realistic skin texture, soft film grain, muted colors, and a raw cinematic atmosphere. The mood should feel tense, quiet, and emotionally heavy, like a moment after chaos. Shot on a vintage anamorphic lens, wide cinematic frame, shallow depth of field, realistic live-action movie still, no text, no logo, no extra characters.",
