     "titleFull": "Ultra-realistic conceptual fashion portrait using the exact",
     "desc": "Ultra-realistic conceptual fashion portrait using the exact same face as the reference image (same eyes, same beard, same hairstyle, same glasses, strict identity lock, no variation).\n\nA young man standing in a minimal studio under strong angled light. His shadow on the wall is fully alive and different, sitting on the ground with a withdrawn, introspective posture.\n\n Face rules:\n\n* identical to reference image\n* no distortion, no reinterpretation\n* same proportions, same gaze, same skin texture\n\n⸻\n\n Outfit (THIS is where virality comes from)\n\nModern high-end streetwear with strong visual contrast:\n\n* cropped black bomber jacket (slightly glossy texture)\n* inner: fitted off-white tee (clean contrast)\n* pants: wide-leg cargos with structure (matte charcoal)\n* sneakers: chunky off-white premium sneakers\n* accessories: thin silver chain + subtle rings\n\nFit should look intentional, styled, not random\n\n⸻\n\n Lighting (make it hit)\n\n* strong side light (45° angle)\n* sharp shadow separation\n* shadow darker, slightly softer edges\n* subtle rim light on subject\n\n⸻\n\n Composition\n\n* subject standing slightly right\n* shadow sitting on left wall\n* clean negative space\n* cinematic balance\n\n⸻\n\n Typography (clean but impactful)\n\n* Top: NOT ME (bold, tight kerning)\n* Below small: BUT STILL ME\n* Bottom integrated in shadow: OTHER (slightly transparent, large)\n\n⸻\n\n Style direction\n\n* luxury campaign aesthetic\n* sharp focus, 8K\n* neutral beige background\n* high contrast but soft skin tones\n\n“editorial fashion campaign, Balenciaga style, high-end streetwear photography”",
